    <compoundname>interrupt_sleep</compoundname>
    <title>Interruptible sleep functions</title>
    <sectiondef kind="func">
      <memberdef kind="function" id="group__interrupt__sleep_1ga3452730f2502295ab9dbcd425f057a64" prot="public" static="no" const="no" explicit="no" inline="no" virt="non-virtual">
        <type>VLC_API int</type>
        <definition>VLC_API int vlc_sem_wait_i11e</definition>
        <argsstring>(vlc_sem_t *)</argsstring>
        <name>vlc_sem_wait_i11e</name>
        <param>
          <type><ref refid="group__thread_1gaefec241da45a9c83371c3a69e5359fb9" kindref="member">vlc_sem_t</ref> *</type>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Interruptible variant of <ref refid="group__thread_1gad690a85e538e894a8646788466a1fcbb" kindref="member">vlc_sem_wait()</ref>.</para>
<para>Waits on a semaphore like <ref refid="group__thread_1gad690a85e538e894a8646788466a1fcbb" kindref="member">vlc_sem_wait()</ref>. If the calling thread has an interruption context (as set by <ref refid="group__interrupt__context_1ga493327cca117b02f4361992444330c71" kindref="member">vlc_interrupt_set()</ref>), and another thread invokes <ref refid="group__interrupt__context_1ga6ad7acf9e5d0639e9e0ffc81b477dc1b" kindref="member">vlc_interrupt_raise()</ref> on that context, the semaphore is incremented.</para>
<para><simplesect kind="warning"><para>The calling thread should be the only thread ever to wait on the specified semaphore. Otherwise, interruptions may not be delivered accurately (the wrong thread may be woken up).</para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="note"><para>This function is (always) a cancellation point.</para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="return"><para>EINTR if the semaphore was incremented due to an interruption, otherwise zero. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
        </inbodydescription>
