      </memberdef>
      <memberdef kind="function" id="group__interrupt__sleep_1gac9afbeb073fe629c591b75d5ff90f140" prot="public" static="no" const="no" explicit="no" inline="no" virt="non-virtual">
        <type>VLC_API int</type>
        <definition>VLC_API int vlc_poll_i11e</definition>
        <argsstring>(struct pollfd *, unsigned, int)</argsstring>
        <name>vlc_poll_i11e</name>
        <param>
          <type>struct pollfd *</type>
        </param>
        <param>
          <type>unsigned</type>
        </param>
        <param>
          <type>int</type>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Interruptible variant of poll().</para>
<para>Waits for file descriptors I/O events, a timeout, a signal or a VLC I/O interruption. Except for VLC I/O interruptions, this function behaves just like the standard poll().</para>
<para><simplesect kind="note"><para>This function is always a cancellation point (as poll()). </para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="see"><para>poll() manual page</para>
</simplesect>
<parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>fds</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>table of events to wait for </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>nfds</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>number of entries in the table </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>timeout</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>time to wait in milliseconds or -1 for infinite</para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para>A strictly positive result represent the number of pending events. 0 is returned if the time-out is reached without events. -1 is returned if a VLC I/O interrupt occurs (and errno is set to EINTR) or if an error occurs. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
        </inbodydescription>
